the spectra / emulator for the rca .wthe rca  emulator system is supplied withthe spectra / as a reprogramming aid.  it allows an rca  object program to be run on the spectra/ without necessitating changes in the rca  object code.  execution rates are considerablybetter than traditional simulation.  the emulator provides an increase in throughput capacity for the user on the spectra /.  the emulator makes use of both hardware micro-program routines andsoftware routines to accomplish its function.cacm december, benjamin, r. i.ca jb march ,   : pm